73
00:04:49,560 --> 00:04:52,080
Today we're going to learn about

74
00:04:52,080 --> 00:04:54,640
the different types of people in organizations.

75
00:04:57,720 --> 00:04:59,480
We can divide them into three categories.

76
00:05:00,480 --> 00:05:01,360
The first type

77
00:05:01,680 --> 00:05:04,240
is called Givers.

78
00:05:04,560 --> 00:05:07,840
These are people who focus on helping others

79
00:05:09,040 --> 00:05:11,320
and making the people around them better.

80
00:05:12,080 --> 00:05:13,480
However, in an organization,

81
00:05:13,480 --> 00:05:16,680
Givers need to be careful.

82
00:05:17,120 --> 00:05:20,080
If they sacrifice ourselves too much

83
00:05:20,080 --> 00:05:23,280
and always put others before ourselves,

84
00:05:23,280 --> 00:05:26,080
it often prevents them from achieving success.

85
00:05:28,560 --> 00:05:29,480
The second group.

86
00:05:30,080 --> 00:05:33,680
The second group is called Takers.

87
00:05:38,080 --> 00:05:39,520
These people focus primarily

88
00:05:39,520 --> 00:05:41,520
on gaining benefits from others

89
00:05:42,320 --> 00:05:43,600
while giving as little as possible in return.

90
00:05:44,320 --> 00:05:46,640
Organizations should be careful

91
00:05:46,640 --> 00:05:48,560
not to have too many people like this.

92
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:53,600
The final group

93
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:57,280
is called Matchers.

94
00:05:57,720 --> 00:06:00,880
These are people who give only when

95
00:06:00,880 --> 00:06:02,920
they receive something

96
00:06:02,920 --> 00:06:04,920
equal or balanced in return.

97
00:06:08,160 --> 00:06:10,280
Successful relationships within organizations

98
00:06:10,280 --> 00:06:12,880
require people who are willing to exchange fairly

99
00:06:12,880 --> 00:06:15,040
and work together

100
00:06:15,040 --> 00:06:16,520
without taking advantage of one another.

101
00:06:16,920 --> 00:06:19,080
Who is that following God Jane?

102
00:06:19,680 --> 00:06:21,040
