282
00:20:17,920 --> 00:20:19,320
How P'Ohm made the national team?

283
00:20:27,560 --> 00:20:28,960
What does that have to do with anything?

284
00:20:31,120 --> 00:20:32,320
Do you really think P'Ohm

285
00:20:32,320 --> 00:20:33,160
was talented enough

286
00:20:33,160 --> 00:20:35,160
to make the national team on his own?

287
00:20:39,240 --> 00:20:40,040
P'Ohm! Pass it here!

288
00:20:49,680 --> 00:20:50,520
Shit!

289
00:20:59,280 --> 00:20:59,920
Right?

290
00:21:01,160 --> 00:21:02,280
Everyone thinks the same thing.

291
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:06,160
It was because of P'Jane

292
00:21:06,840 --> 00:21:08,200
that P'Ohm made the national team.

293
00:21:10,400 --> 00:21:11,360
After that,

294
00:21:12,200 --> 00:21:13,920
the sports car P'Ohm loved so much

295
00:21:14,160 --> 00:21:16,160
got taken away.

296
00:21:16,600 --> 00:21:17,560
The sports car?

297
00:21:18,160 --> 00:21:21,040
Wait, the one he was super protective of?

298
00:21:22,480 --> 00:21:24,480
At first P'Ohm refused to give it up,

299
00:21:24,960 --> 00:21:27,360
but P'Jane managed to take it anyway.

300
00:21:30,280 --> 00:21:31,280
After that,

301
00:21:31,440 --> 00:21:32,680
P'Ohm became terrified of him,

302
00:21:32,680 --> 00:21:34,680
just like you've seen.

303
00:21:36,280 --> 00:21:37,520
P'Jane, I'm sorry.

304
00:21:38,480 --> 00:21:39,640
I didn't mean to.

305
00:21:43,680 --> 00:21:45,480
And what were the conditions of the deal?

306
00:21:48,080 --> 00:21:49,280
There was only one condition.

307
00:21:50,960 --> 00:21:52,720
If you ask him for something

308
00:21:53,080 --> 00:21:54,080
and he gives it to you,

309
00:21:56,520 --> 00:21:58,800
he can ask for anything from you in return.

310
00:21:59,680 --> 00:22:00,320
Anything.

311
00:22:01,840 --> 00:22:03,000
And you have to give it to him,

312
00:22:03,000 --> 00:22:03,840
you can't refuse.

313
00:22:05,040 --> 00:22:06,640
What does he even gain from doing that?

314
00:22:09,280 --> 00:22:10,120
I don't know.

315
00:22:10,880 --> 00:22:12,440
But he always does this.

316
00:22:14,040 --> 00:22:15,240
He messes with your head

317
00:22:15,480 --> 00:22:17,040
until you believe you're special.

318
00:22:18,280 --> 00:22:19,320
And once you believe it,

319
00:22:20,120 --> 00:22:22,120
you'll start asking him for things,

320
00:22:22,480 --> 00:22:24,200
then you'll make a deal with him.

321
00:22:28,480 --> 00:22:29,880
He hasn't said anything like that to you,

322
00:22:29,880 --> 00:22:31,040
right?

323
00:22:35,360 --> 00:22:37,480
You're far more special than I ever imagined.

324
00:22:39,680 --> 00:22:41,480
More special than anyone I've ever met.

325
00:22:43,280 --> 00:22:44,200
So...

326
00:22:46,120 --> 00:22:47,560
don't fall for him

327
00:22:47,560 --> 00:22:49,280
and don't make any deals with him.

328
00:22:49,840 --> 00:22:51,480
Otherwise he'll come to collect.

329
00:22:55,440 --> 00:22:57,360
You know I don't trust people easily.

330
00:22:58,160 --> 00:22:58,960
You don't know anything.

331
00:23:01,720 --> 00:23:03,640
He graduated in psychology from Harvard.

332
00:23:04,560 --> 00:23:06,120
Huh? Harvard?

333
00:23:07,680 --> 00:23:08,480
No way.

334
00:23:09,280 --> 00:23:09,880
If that were true,

335
00:23:09,880 --> 00:23:10,880
he would've told me already.

336
00:23:10,880 --> 00:23:12,640
That's because he's manipulating you.

337
00:23:13,320 --> 00:23:14,280
And you know what else?

338
00:23:14,760 --> 00:23:16,520
He's actually twenty-seven years old.

339
00:23:16,520 --> 00:23:17,240
That's enough.

340
00:23:18,240 --> 00:23:19,640
You just love talking shit.

341
00:23:20,040 --> 00:23:21,080
Do you even have proof?

342
00:23:23,520 --> 00:23:25,080
How did you become this kind of person?

343
00:23:27,240 --> 00:23:28,480
Because you're stupid like this,

344
00:23:28,680 --> 00:23:30,040
that's why he can trick you!

345
00:23:30,480 --> 00:23:31,360
What about you?

346
00:23:31,760 --> 00:23:32,560
You think you're so great?

347
00:23:32,840 --> 00:23:33,800
How can you become such a shitty person

348
00:23:33,800 --> 00:23:34,960
and go around slandering people like that?

349
00:23:35,320 --> 00:23:36,120
Fine!!

350
00:23:36,320 --> 00:23:37,880
Then I hope he tricks you

351
00:23:38,040 --> 00:23:38,960
until your whole life falls apart!

352
00:23:39,960 --> 00:23:41,200
What the hell is wrong with you, Put?

353
00:23:41,200 --> 00:23:41,960
Shit!

354
00:23:42,320 --> 00:23:43,120
Shit!

355
00:23:45,480 --> 00:23:46,880
Why'd you punch him?

356
00:23:50,440 --> 00:23:51,640
Jane, what's wrong with you?

357
00:23:59,480 --> 00:24:00,360
Huh?

358
00:24:00,840 --> 00:24:01,320
Jane?

359
00:24:15,880 --> 00:24:17,360
Is there something bothering you?

360
00:24:19,640 --> 00:24:20,440
Hmm?

361
00:24:22,720 --> 00:24:23,640
You've been so quiet,

362
00:24:23,640 --> 00:24:25,640
not as cheerful as usual.

363
00:24:32,280 --> 00:24:33,560
A lot of people don't like you.

364
00:24:36,520 --> 00:24:37,320
Really?

365
00:24:38,680 --> 00:24:39,480
Like who?

366
00:24:44,440 --> 00:24:46,680
My friends.

367
00:24:49,240 --> 00:24:50,040
Your friends?

368
00:24:53,680 --> 00:24:56,080
Why do you seem completely unbothered?

369
00:24:57,880 --> 00:24:59,280
Doesn't it affect you at all?

370
00:25:03,080 --> 00:25:04,720
You mean the way people see me?

371
00:25:07,080 --> 00:25:08,840
I've heard some of the rumors.

372
00:25:10,680 --> 00:25:12,480
But rumors are just rumors.

373
00:25:13,760 --> 00:25:14,960
That's why they don't bother me.

374
00:25:48,000 --> 00:25:48,920
May I see your driver's license?

375
00:25:48,920 --> 00:25:50,480
And please take a breathalyzer test.

376
00:26:12,920 --> 00:26:14,960
Actually, he's already twenty-seven.

377
00:26:14,960 --> 00:26:15,760
That's enough.

378
00:26:28,520 --> 00:26:29,560
Do you have a wound?

379
00:26:37,280 --> 00:26:38,280
What happened?

380
00:26:40,680 --> 00:26:41,680
What poked you?

381
00:26:50,080 --> 00:26:51,280
A splinter.

382
00:26:55,680 --> 00:26:56,840
But I already took it out.

383
00:27:04,440 --> 00:27:05,120
Everything's good.

384
00:27:05,760 --> 00:27:06,680
You may proceed.

385
00:27:07,680 --> 00:27:08,680
You may proceed, thank you.

386
00:27:44,680 --> 00:27:46,040
Is this what's bothering you?

387
00:27:58,920 --> 00:27:59,760
You know,

388
00:28:02,280 --> 00:28:04,080
I've never fought with a friend before.

389
00:28:07,360 --> 00:28:09,000
But today I punched my best friend

390
00:28:09,000 --> 00:28:09,920
to defend you.

391
00:28:12,080 --> 00:28:13,240
You got into a fight?

392
00:28:15,360 --> 00:28:16,160
Yeah.

393
00:28:18,960 --> 00:28:20,960
Is there anything you want to tell me?

394
00:28:22,360 --> 00:28:23,760
About the things you lied to me about.

395
00:28:27,280 --> 00:28:28,680
Like your age.

396
00:28:30,680 --> 00:28:31,920
And Harvard.

397
00:28:35,520 --> 00:28:36,600
I didn't tell you

398
00:28:37,960 --> 00:28:38,560
because I didn't think

399
00:28:38,560 --> 00:28:39,880
that graduating from Harvard

400
00:28:39,880 --> 00:28:41,160
with a psychology degree

401
00:28:42,320 --> 00:28:43,080
had anything to do

402
00:28:43,080 --> 00:28:44,280
with our relationship.

403
00:28:46,960 --> 00:28:48,560
Is there anything else you want to know?

404
00:28:59,320 --> 00:29:01,160
Did you take P'Ohm's sports car?

405
00:29:02,520 --> 00:29:03,600
I wasn't the one who took it.

406
00:29:07,600 --> 00:29:09,320
Did you send Tee to prison?

407
00:29:11,720 --> 00:29:12,800
Tee went to prison

408
00:29:13,520 --> 00:29:14,920
because he embezzled university funds.

409
00:29:16,120 --> 00:29:17,720
And have you ever made deals with people?

410
00:29:18,760 --> 00:29:19,880
Deals where you can demand

411
00:29:19,880 --> 00:29:21,440
anything back from them?

412
00:29:26,120 --> 00:29:26,920
Do you know

413
00:29:29,360 --> 00:29:32,480
the difference between help and a favor?

414
00:29:35,320 --> 00:29:36,120
What's the difference?

415
00:29:37,920 --> 00:29:40,960
Help is simply helping someone.

416
00:29:42,920 --> 00:29:44,280
But a favor

417
00:29:44,840 --> 00:29:46,240
is more like a business transaction.

418
00:29:46,680 --> 00:29:47,440
It's helping someone,

419
00:29:47,440 --> 00:29:49,320
but there is an expectation of repayment.

420
00:29:50,120 --> 00:29:52,360
That's why I make formal agreements.

421
00:29:54,600 --> 00:29:56,160
Since both parties agree to it,

422
00:29:57,600 --> 00:29:58,520
if I ask for repayment later,

423
00:29:58,520 --> 00:29:59,640
there's nothing wrong with that, right?

424
00:30:30,640 --> 00:30:32,320
I think I should go to your house.

425
00:30:33,920 --> 00:30:34,720
Huh?

426
00:30:37,120 --> 00:30:37,920
Why?

427
00:30:39,880 --> 00:30:41,240
To introduce myself to your family.

428
00:30:42,000 --> 00:30:43,040
As your talking-stage partner.

429
00:31:05,760 --> 00:31:06,560
Who is that?

430
00:31:06,720 --> 00:31:07,520
I don't know.

431
00:31:11,280 --> 00:31:12,080
Hello.

432
00:31:16,120 --> 00:31:17,640
Hello, sir and ma'am.

433
00:31:18,240 --> 00:31:19,680
Hello.

434
00:31:19,920 --> 00:31:20,720
Hello.

435
00:31:21,720 --> 00:31:22,520
Dad, Mom.

436
00:31:22,960 --> 00:31:24,960
This is P'Jane.

437
00:31:25,400 --> 00:31:27,320
He's a fourth year in my faculty.

438
00:31:27,560 --> 00:31:28,360
Oh.

439
00:31:28,360 --> 00:31:29,160
Oh.

440
00:31:30,720 --> 00:31:32,480
At university, everyone calls him

441
00:31:33,720 --> 00:31:34,520
Big Jane.

442
00:31:35,920 --> 00:31:36,720
Same name.

443
00:31:38,960 --> 00:31:40,320
I'm Jane Patrick.

444
00:31:46,840 --> 00:31:48,320
I'm Jane's talking-stage partner.

445
00:31:51,720 --> 00:31:52,720
Ah..

446
00:31:53,520 --> 00:31:54,160
Oh.

447
00:31:54,360 --> 00:31:55,360
Um..

448
00:31:59,320 --> 00:32:00,200
I see.

449
00:32:01,120 --> 00:32:03,880
Well then, make yourself at home.

450
00:32:04,920 --> 00:32:06,400
Thank you for bringing Jane home.

451
00:32:06,760 --> 00:32:07,560
You're welcome.

452
00:32:10,120 --> 00:32:11,400
Oh, and this is...

453
00:32:12,560 --> 00:32:13,680
Jean, my younger sister.

454
00:32:14,480 --> 00:32:14,960
Oh.

455
00:32:15,040 --> 00:32:17,320
Is he the one you made the gift for?

456
00:32:17,320 --> 00:32:17,920
Shhh!

457
00:32:18,280 --> 00:32:18,840
Jean.

458
00:32:29,280 --> 00:32:30,280
Please make yourself comfortable.

459
00:32:32,520 --> 00:32:33,120
Jane?

460
00:32:33,520 --> 00:32:34,400
Yes, Mom?

461
00:32:34,880 --> 00:32:35,920
I think that...

462
00:32:36,440 --> 00:32:38,120
this one looks good..

463
00:32:38,120 --> 00:32:40,240
a lot more handsome than the last guy.

464
00:32:43,720 --> 00:32:44,520
Mom.

465
00:32:44,760 --> 00:32:47,040
Wow, there are so many orders today.

466
00:32:47,680 --> 00:32:50,920
Help me sort out the herbs.

467
00:32:53,320 --> 00:32:54,120
Sure.

468
00:32:58,520 --> 00:32:59,400
What were you two talking about?

469
00:33:03,280 --> 00:33:04,080
Nothing.

470
00:33:29,720 --> 00:33:31,080
Is there anything I can help with?

471
00:33:32,120 --> 00:33:33,080
It's okay.

472
00:33:34,280 --> 00:33:35,360
But I want to help.

473
00:33:36,200 --> 00:33:36,880
I can help.

474
00:33:38,600 --> 00:33:39,360
Well then...

475
00:33:40,320 --> 00:33:41,640
Could you get me ten grams of dang gui?

476
00:33:41,960 --> 00:33:42,640
Ten grams?

477
00:33:54,480 --> 00:33:55,720
It'll be impressive if he finds it.

478
00:34:03,880 --> 00:34:04,760
Here it is.

479
00:34:06,000 --> 00:34:06,800
It's this one.

480
00:34:14,960 --> 00:34:16,880
Do people normally eat the whole root like this?

481
00:34:17,520 --> 00:34:19,520
No, you have to boil it first.

482
00:34:20,520 --> 00:34:21,320
Oh.

483
00:34:21,760 --> 00:34:22,560
Ten grams.

484
00:34:50,120 --> 00:34:51,159
Isn't that a bit much?

485
00:35:19,320 --> 00:35:20,120
See?

486
00:35:20,680 --> 00:35:21,680
It's easy.

487
00:35:29,720 --> 00:35:32,240
Why don't you use a digital scale?

488
00:35:33,520 --> 00:35:35,000
We bought one before.

489
00:35:35,840 --> 00:35:37,320
But my parents aren't used to it.

490
00:35:37,920 --> 00:35:38,720
There.

491
00:35:44,360 --> 00:35:45,160
Mm.

492
00:35:45,960 --> 00:35:46,800
Put that away for me too.

493
00:36:01,480 --> 00:36:02,920
Want to try slicing some?

494
00:36:12,320 --> 00:36:13,000
Sure.

495
00:36:16,520 --> 00:36:17,320
Are you sure?

496
00:36:18,200 --> 00:36:19,320
If you're not used to it,

497
00:36:19,920 --> 00:36:21,080
you might hurt yourself.

498
00:36:23,720 --> 00:36:24,520
I can do it.

499
00:36:37,560 --> 00:36:38,280
You

500
00:36:39,680 --> 00:36:40,480
You're kinda stubborn.

501
00:36:40,480 --> 00:36:41,280
Oh.

502
00:36:41,280 --> 00:36:42,080
Hey!

503
00:37:00,920 --> 00:37:02,520
So when he's at university,

504
00:37:03,560 --> 00:37:04,800
what's Jane like?

505
00:37:06,520 --> 00:37:07,320
Mom.

506
00:37:07,320 --> 00:37:07,840
What?

507
00:37:08,520 --> 00:37:10,240
I just want to know.

508
00:37:12,120 --> 00:37:13,000
He's adorable.

509
00:37:17,400 --> 00:37:19,400
Jane is always helping everyone.

510
00:37:21,160 --> 00:37:23,120
That's why I thought he was cute.

511
00:37:25,240 --> 00:37:26,360
Mm.

512
00:37:27,280 --> 00:37:29,520
He's always been a good kid.

513
00:37:31,120 --> 00:37:32,160
Whenever anyone asked him for something,

514
00:37:32,160 --> 00:37:33,880
or whenever we wanted him to do something,

515
00:37:34,320 --> 00:37:35,840
he never refused.

516
00:37:40,280 --> 00:37:41,920
Out of all my children,

517
00:37:43,000 --> 00:37:44,520
he's the one I worry about the most.

518
00:37:45,280 --> 00:37:46,080
Mom...

519
00:37:46,960 --> 00:37:47,960
Aww.

520
00:37:48,560 --> 00:37:49,960
I worry because

521
00:37:52,520 --> 00:37:53,760
he's such a kind person.

522
00:37:54,160 --> 00:37:55,560
And a bit absent-minded too.

523
00:37:56,000 --> 00:37:56,840
Hey!

524
00:37:57,520 --> 00:37:58,520
Quite forgetful.

525
00:37:59,680 --> 00:38:01,920
Back when he was little,

526
00:38:02,320 --> 00:38:04,440
I used to make sweet ginkgo dessert soup

527
00:38:04,920 --> 00:38:06,760
to help improve his memory.

528
00:38:07,280 --> 00:38:08,440
But every time I wasn't looking,

529
00:38:08,440 --> 00:38:10,280
he'd secretly pour it away.

530
00:38:11,320 --> 00:38:12,840
Because ginkgo is bitter.

531
00:38:15,960 --> 00:38:16,880
The ginkgo?

532
00:38:18,080 --> 00:38:19,880
The one we just prepared together?

533
00:38:20,920 --> 00:38:21,520
Yeah.

534
00:38:21,920 --> 00:38:23,080
The one we made earlier.

535
00:38:23,880 --> 00:38:26,720
And you almost destroyed the counter with it.

536
00:38:33,560 --> 00:38:35,160
Give me some credit, okay?

537
00:38:43,400 --> 00:38:44,760
Thank you so much for today.

538
00:38:45,160 --> 00:38:45,680
Mm.

539
00:38:46,120 --> 00:38:47,120
The food is delicious.

540
00:38:49,560 --> 00:38:51,280
Please let me help clear the dishes.

541
00:38:52,280 --> 00:38:53,120
Woah.

542
00:38:56,280 --> 00:38:57,680
You know how to wash dishes too?

543
00:39:00,000 --> 00:39:01,720
Doesn't your house have a dishwasher?

544
00:39:02,640 --> 00:39:03,240
Oh.

545
00:39:05,920 --> 00:39:07,000
Oh.

546
00:39:08,320 --> 00:39:11,320
We don't have a dishwasher here.

547
00:39:12,360 --> 00:39:13,560
Please excuse me.

548
00:39:13,560 --> 00:39:14,240
(Thanapat Piboonosot)

549
00:39:14,240 --> 00:39:15,480
Good luck.

550
00:39:15,480 --> 00:39:16,560
Thank you so much for today.

551
00:39:16,920 --> 00:39:17,680
You're welcome.

552
00:39:18,200 --> 00:39:19,240
Come visit again sometime.

553
00:39:19,920 --> 00:39:21,560
And help Jane sort the herbs again.

554
00:39:21,560 --> 00:39:22,600
Mom!

555
00:39:23,720 --> 00:39:24,560
Come visit again.

556
00:39:25,800 --> 00:39:26,920
Go on in.

557
00:39:27,400 --> 00:39:28,200
Bye-bye.

558
00:39:37,320 --> 00:39:38,120
P'Jane.

559
00:39:39,120 --> 00:39:41,480
Wait outside for a moment, okay?

560
00:39:42,240 --> 00:39:44,440
I have something for you.

561
00:39:51,880 --> 00:39:53,080
Is this your car?

562
00:39:59,480 --> 00:40:00,480
You're Jet, right?

563
00:40:01,720 --> 00:40:04,240
Jane talks about you all the time.

564
00:40:04,920 --> 00:40:06,080
Oh.

565
00:40:06,520 --> 00:40:08,600
You're the one who borrowed my outfit, right?

566
00:40:09,800 --> 00:40:11,680
Can I take a picture of your car?

567
00:40:13,760 --> 00:40:14,560
Of course.

568
00:40:15,120 --> 00:40:15,920
Thank you.

569
00:40:19,040 --> 00:40:22,520
(Thanapat Piboonosot)

570
00:40:32,720 --> 00:40:33,880
How much does this car cost?

571
00:40:39,200 --> 00:40:40,000
Do you want one?

572
00:40:40,720 --> 00:40:41,880
Of course I do.

573
00:40:42,160 --> 00:40:43,400
It's so cool.

574
00:40:44,360 --> 00:40:45,520
I've always dreamed

575
00:40:46,320 --> 00:40:48,280
to own a supercar like this someday

576
00:40:48,920 --> 00:40:50,720
would be so amazing.

577
00:40:53,800 --> 00:40:56,400
I think you'd look great driving a supercar.

578
00:41:00,520 --> 00:41:01,840
Are you going to let me drive it?

579
00:41:02,760 --> 00:41:04,000
Why borrow one?

580
00:41:07,560 --> 00:41:09,000
You should have your own.

581
00:41:11,920 --> 00:41:13,120
If that's what you want,

582
00:41:15,680 --> 00:41:17,400
I can get you a supercar of your own.

583
00:41:26,920 --> 00:41:27,920
Hey, Jet.

584
00:41:28,880 --> 00:41:30,600
Dad and Mom saved some food for you in the kitchen.

585
00:41:31,600 --> 00:41:32,720
Mm, okay.

586
00:41:35,320 --> 00:41:36,120
I'm heading out now.

587
00:41:41,000 --> 00:41:42,160
What were you two talking about?

588
00:41:43,320 --> 00:41:43,800
Nothing.

589
00:41:44,720 --> 00:41:46,080
Nothing, we were just introducing ourselves.

590
00:41:50,400 --> 00:41:53,160
Looks like everyone in my family likes you.

591
00:41:54,680 --> 00:41:55,560
What about you?

592
00:41:56,480 --> 00:41:57,520
Do you feel better now?

593
00:42:00,320 --> 00:42:01,160
Yeah.

594
00:42:04,800 --> 00:42:06,120
And about your friend...

595
00:42:09,120 --> 00:42:09,960
Don't worry.

596
00:42:11,160 --> 00:42:12,600
I'll handle it myself.

597
00:42:17,320 --> 00:42:18,320
Thank you.

598
00:42:19,760 --> 00:42:21,200
For standing by my side.

599
00:42:25,920 --> 00:42:27,360
If there's anything you want to ask me,

600
00:42:30,120 --> 00:42:31,480
just ask.

601
00:42:34,920 --> 00:42:36,360
I'm willing to prove anything.

602
00:42:44,120 --> 00:42:45,920
So what was it that you wanted to give me?

603
00:43:08,160 --> 00:43:11,080
I told my dad that you get migraines.

604
00:43:13,320 --> 00:43:15,760
So Dad said

605
00:43:15,760 --> 00:43:17,160
your blood circulation might not be very good

606
00:43:18,160 --> 00:43:20,320
and that you should drink dang gui often.

607
00:43:21,800 --> 00:43:22,480
Here.

608
00:43:23,760 --> 00:43:26,920
I wrote down all the instructions for you.

609
00:43:26,920 --> 00:43:28,280
(Steps for preparing dang gui tea)

610
00:43:28,280 --> 00:43:29,680
I'm worried you won't know how to prepare it.

611
00:43:30,360 --> 00:43:31,880
You might end up eating the whole sheet.

612
00:44:13,120 --> 00:44:16,520
(I followed all your instructions.)

613
00:44:18,920 --> 00:44:20,480
I told the professor so many times.

614
00:44:20,480 --> 00:44:22,920
I wasn't sleeping, I was listening.

615
00:44:23,320 --> 00:44:24,600
I saw you dozing off.

616
00:44:25,680 --> 00:44:27,200
How could you see that? I wasn't asleep.

617
00:44:27,720 --> 00:44:29,480
Because I saw you, you were even snoring.

618
00:44:32,440 --> 00:44:34,160
Hey, isn't that Put's bike?

619
00:44:51,040 --> 00:44:52,480
Shit.

620
00:44:55,520 --> 00:44:56,760
What happened, Put?

621
00:44:58,200 --> 00:44:59,160
Who did this to you?

622
00:45:00,720 --> 00:45:02,320
You already know who did it.

623
00:45:03,120 --> 00:45:04,320
Don't worry about me.

624
00:45:17,960 --> 00:45:18,960
Sweetheart.

625
00:45:19,320 --> 00:45:22,960
I brought you flowers.

626
00:45:22,960 --> 00:45:24,520
You can open your eyes now.

627
00:45:24,520 --> 00:45:25,920
Wow, thank you.

628
00:45:46,600 --> 00:45:48,480
For Valentine's Day, Jane.

629
00:45:50,960 --> 00:45:52,240
Thank you.

630
00:46:04,480 --> 00:46:05,280
They smell amazing.

631
00:46:05,960 --> 00:46:07,080
What flowers are these?

632
00:46:08,400 --> 00:46:09,720
I've never seen them before.

633
00:46:10,920 --> 00:46:11,920
Lilacs.

634
00:46:13,800 --> 00:46:15,640
Their meaning is

635
00:46:17,320 --> 00:46:18,280
first love.

636
00:46:31,200 --> 00:46:32,520
Since earlier.

637
00:46:32,960 --> 00:46:34,320
Is there something wrong?

638
00:46:47,640 --> 00:46:50,080
I just think your surprise is way too much.

639
00:46:52,960 --> 00:46:53,600
It feels like

640
00:46:53,600 --> 00:46:54,600
more than a talking-stage relationship.

641
00:46:54,600 --> 00:46:55,720
More than what people at this relationship do.

642
00:46:59,280 --> 00:47:00,400
This isn't over the top at all.

643
00:47:01,520 --> 00:47:03,200
If it makes you happy,

644
00:47:04,680 --> 00:47:06,320
I can do even more.

645
00:47:09,680 --> 00:47:12,120
But it makes me afraid to give you my gift.

646
00:47:16,920 --> 00:47:18,120
What if you're disappointed?

647
00:47:44,520 --> 00:47:46,320
It's my first time making something like this.

648
00:47:49,520 --> 00:47:50,800
I don't even know if it turned out well.

649
00:48:05,920 --> 00:48:06,720
P'Jane.

650
00:48:18,120 --> 00:48:19,360
I'm not disappointed at all.

651
00:48:22,280 --> 00:48:23,120
I love it.

652
00:48:27,200 --> 00:48:28,000
Really?

653
00:48:30,480 --> 00:48:31,280
Of course.

654
00:48:32,840 --> 00:48:34,720
You made this yourself, didn't you?

655
00:48:35,760 --> 00:48:36,560
Yeah.

656
00:48:44,160 --> 00:48:46,120
So the wound on your finger that day...

657
00:48:48,520 --> 00:48:49,200
Yeah.

658
00:48:50,120 --> 00:48:51,640
I got poked by a sewing needle.

659
00:48:53,520 --> 00:48:54,320
I thought

660
00:48:54,840 --> 00:48:55,720
if there was something you wanted,

661
00:48:55,720 --> 00:48:57,720
you probably already have it.

662
00:48:57,720 --> 00:48:59,040
So I wanted to make something

663
00:48:59,760 --> 00:49:01,400
that's one of a kind.

664
00:49:08,000 --> 00:49:08,800
That's true.

665
00:49:11,160 --> 00:49:13,120
Normally nobody gives me anything.

666
00:49:15,800 --> 00:49:16,920
People only come to ask me for things.

667
00:49:28,400 --> 00:49:29,680
I really like it.

668
00:49:33,320 --> 00:49:34,320
Thank you, Jane.

669
00:49:35,480 --> 00:49:36,480
Yeah.

670
00:49:38,000 --> 00:49:39,200
I have something else to show you.

671
00:49:45,360 --> 00:49:46,720
I drew this myself.

672
00:49:47,720 --> 00:49:48,600
Is it pretty?

673
00:49:53,760 --> 00:49:55,360
Is this the drawing you're submitting to the competition?

674
00:49:57,280 --> 00:49:58,920
The person in the picture is you in both versions.

675
00:49:59,880 --> 00:50:00,680
Yeah.

676
00:50:02,200 --> 00:50:03,720
The competition theme is

677
00:50:06,320 --> 00:50:07,920
the person we trust, right?

678
00:50:11,680 --> 00:50:14,080
I think from now on, I'll trust myself.

679
00:50:17,720 --> 00:50:19,120
Because you're the one who taught me

680
00:50:19,120 --> 00:50:20,560
to believe in myself.

681
00:50:23,280 --> 00:50:24,880
That's why I had the courage to submit it.

682
00:50:29,480 --> 00:50:30,720
I'm happy

683
00:50:32,400 --> 00:50:34,320
that I could inspire you.

684
00:50:38,040 --> 00:50:39,520
It's Valentine's Day.

685
00:50:40,040 --> 00:50:41,240
Can you not go home

686
00:50:42,360 --> 00:50:44,720
and stay at my condo for one night?

687
00:50:48,600 --> 00:50:49,400
I'd like to,

688
00:50:50,680 --> 00:50:53,160
but I have a psychology quiz tomorrow.

689
00:50:54,960 --> 00:50:55,760
And it's a difficult one.

690
00:50:56,200 --> 00:50:57,800
I still have a lot of studying to do.

691
00:50:59,320 --> 00:51:00,800
Then why don't I tutor you?

692
00:51:02,560 --> 00:51:03,480
You know,

693
00:51:03,920 --> 00:51:06,040
I graduated in psychology from Harvard.

694
00:51:08,200 --> 00:51:09,480
And once we're done studying,

695
00:51:11,040 --> 00:51:12,680
you can stay over at my place.

696
00:51:13,800 --> 00:51:15,200
That way you won't have to travel back and forth.

697
00:51:15,200 --> 00:51:15,760
Huh?

698
00:51:16,560 --> 00:51:17,360
Stay over?

699
00:51:17,360 --> 00:51:18,520
You don't want to?

700
00:51:29,920 --> 00:51:31,320
Because I want you

701
00:51:36,000 --> 00:51:37,280
to stay with me tonight.

702
00:52:03,760 --> 00:52:05,040
Mm.

703
00:52:18,320 --> 00:52:20,320
According to Cognitive Dissonance Theory,

704
00:52:21,040 --> 00:52:23,280
developed by Leon Festinger,

705
00:52:23,960 --> 00:52:25,760
we tend to feel uncomfortable

706
00:52:25,760 --> 00:52:27,240
when our behavior conflicts

707
00:52:27,240 --> 00:52:29,240
with the attitudes or beliefs we hold.

708
00:52:32,120 --> 00:52:33,840
Based on this theory,

709
00:52:35,320 --> 00:52:37,280
if our behavior is inconsistent

710
00:52:37,280 --> 00:52:38,320
with our attitudes,

711
00:52:38,880 --> 00:52:40,720
what would we change, and why?

712
00:52:49,280 --> 00:52:50,920
We would change our attitude

713
00:52:50,920 --> 00:52:52,920
to match our behavior,

714
00:52:53,760 --> 00:52:56,560
because the behavior has already happened

715
00:52:56,560 --> 00:52:58,560
and can't be changed.

716
00:53:03,040 --> 00:53:04,320
Very good.

717
00:53:12,800 --> 00:53:13,920
Let's continue studying.

718
00:53:20,160 --> 00:53:20,880
Actually, I think we should study

719
00:53:20,880 --> 00:53:21,960
something else first.

720
00:53:26,080 --> 00:53:27,520
What do you mean?

721
00:53:59,520 --> 00:54:00,840
P'Jane, what are you doing?

722
00:55:26,800 --> 00:55:27,600
What are you doing?

723
00:55:33,240 --> 00:55:34,040
Hey.

724
00:55:34,240 --> 00:55:35,040
Hey.

725
00:55:35,040 --> 00:55:35,840
Ow.

726
00:56:54,720 --> 00:56:55,520
P'Jane.

727
00:56:56,520 --> 00:56:57,320
P'Jane.

728
00:57:00,120 --> 00:57:01,800
If we go any further...

729
00:57:03,080 --> 00:57:03,920
I've never...

730
00:57:06,920 --> 00:57:08,240
Then tonight, we'll only go as far as you're

731
00:57:08,240 --> 00:57:10,240
comfortable with.

732
00:57:12,600 --> 00:57:14,880
And if there's any point where you're not ready,

733
00:57:18,120 --> 00:57:19,640
I won't force you.

734
00:57:25,400 --> 00:57:26,280
Mm.

735
00:58:10,840 --> 00:58:12,120
Do you want me to stop?

736
00:58:15,400 --> 00:58:16,200
No.

737
00:58:51,840 --> 00:58:52,680
(When thoughts and behaviors conflict,)

738
00:58:52,680 --> 00:58:53,520
(psychological discomfort occurs.)

739
00:58:53,520 --> 00:58:54,360
(The mind then creates defense mechanisms)

740
00:58:54,360 --> 00:58:54,920
(to reduce that conflict.)

741
01:00:03,160 --> 01:00:05,000
I thought you said we were only studying.

742
01:00:07,360 --> 01:00:09,120
Well, I'm not only good at tutoring.

743
01:00:14,080 --> 01:00:15,320
Oh really?

744
01:00:18,520 --> 01:00:19,920
What else are you good at?

745
01:00:26,000 --> 01:00:27,680
I'm pretty good at magic tricks.

746
01:00:34,840 --> 01:00:36,520
Like this.

747
01:00:42,720 --> 01:00:44,400
Here.

748
01:00:45,480 --> 01:00:46,480
Is this for me?

749
01:00:48,920 --> 01:00:49,720
Mm-hmm.

750
01:01:01,800 --> 01:01:02,600
Thank you.

751
01:01:08,520 --> 01:01:10,200
From now on,

752
01:01:11,360 --> 01:01:13,560
this room belongs to you too.

753
01:01:24,920 --> 01:01:27,400
I'm going to the bathroom for a second.

754
01:01:29,080 --> 01:01:29,920
Okay.

755
01:03:36,120 --> 01:03:37,880
What are you doing?

756
01:03:42,720 --> 01:03:44,480
Oh.

757
01:03:45,080 --> 01:03:45,800
Well...

758
01:03:46,840 --> 01:03:48,120
I was walking past

759
01:03:49,160 --> 01:03:51,320
and thought the design looked nice.

760
01:03:51,880 --> 01:03:53,680
Give it to me.

761
01:04:10,160 --> 01:04:11,560
You should hurry to the bathroom

762
01:04:12,960 --> 01:04:14,400
and come back to me.

763
01:04:16,480 --> 01:04:18,320
I already miss holding you.

764
01:04:44,720 --> 01:04:46,200
So? Could you do it?

765
01:04:46,800 --> 01:04:47,600
It was fine.

766
01:04:48,320 --> 01:04:49,760
I studied with P'Jane.

767
01:04:49,760 --> 01:04:51,080
I can tell.

768
01:04:51,800 --> 01:04:53,760
You probably studied until sunrise.

769
01:04:53,760 --> 01:04:54,800
You've been smiling

770
01:04:54,800 --> 01:04:55,760
since before the exam started.

771
01:04:55,760 --> 01:04:57,400
And you're still smiling now.

772
01:05:00,920 --> 01:05:02,120
What are you going on about?

773
01:05:02,120 --> 01:05:02,920
I'm going to the bathroom.

774
01:05:02,920 --> 01:05:04,200
Whoa.

775
01:05:04,680 --> 01:05:07,320
Wait, seriously.

776
01:05:07,320 --> 01:05:08,960
You're okay with P'Jane, right?

777
01:05:10,440 --> 01:05:14,080
You're not overthinking what Put said, are you?

778
01:05:21,480 --> 01:05:22,200
Honestly,

779
01:05:22,200 --> 01:05:23,920
I don't know him very well.

780
01:05:24,680 --> 01:05:26,320
But if you think he's okay,

781
01:05:27,040 --> 01:05:28,160
then I'm relieved.

782
01:05:30,400 --> 01:05:31,200
I'm okay.

783
01:05:32,520 --> 01:05:33,480
Thank you so much.

784
01:05:35,320 --> 01:05:36,520
So when are you two going to be official?

785
01:05:37,480 --> 01:05:38,320
You look so good together.

786
01:05:38,720 --> 01:05:39,920
And you're completely into him.

787
01:05:40,560 --> 01:05:43,480
There you go again, smiling.

788
01:05:43,760 --> 01:05:44,880
Gap! Hey.

789
01:05:52,840 --> 01:05:54,080
Put.

790
01:05:56,760 --> 01:05:58,960
How's your bigbike?

791
01:06:12,840 --> 01:06:14,120
You should give him some time.

792
01:06:14,720 --> 01:06:16,360
Honestly, he's really worried about you.

793
01:06:25,080 --> 01:06:26,200
I'm going to the bathroom.

794
01:07:29,600 --> 01:07:30,400
Jui?

795
01:07:30,960 --> 01:07:32,360
How did you get in here?

796
01:07:32,360 --> 01:07:33,000
Jane.

797
01:07:33,760 --> 01:07:34,560
Jane.

798
01:07:35,200 --> 01:07:36,560
Please tell P'Jane.

799
01:07:36,680 --> 01:07:38,080
not to let Champ come after me anymore.

800
01:07:38,200 --> 01:07:39,720
Otherwise I'm really going to die.

801
01:07:40,000 --> 01:07:40,800
Please, Jane.

802
01:07:41,320 --> 01:07:42,320
What are you talking about?

803
01:07:42,960 --> 01:07:43,720
You really don't know

804
01:07:43,720 --> 01:07:45,520
what P'Jane has done?

805
01:07:48,360 --> 01:07:49,520
What do you mean?

806
01:07:50,080 --> 01:07:51,320
What did he do?

807
01:07:51,920 --> 01:07:53,680
Aren't you dating him?

808
01:07:53,680 --> 01:07:54,720
How could you not know

809
01:07:54,720 --> 01:07:55,840
all the things he's done?

810
01:07:55,840 --> 01:07:57,400
Please help me.

811
01:07:57,520 --> 01:07:58,720
I don't know anything.

812
01:07:58,720 --> 01:08:00,120
How am I supposed to help?

813
01:08:00,560 --> 01:08:01,360
What the hell?

814
01:08:01,360 --> 01:08:03,120
Are you dumb or being played?

815
01:08:03,520 --> 01:08:04,320
That's enough.

816
01:08:05,120 --> 01:08:06,040
Why does everyone keep acting like

817
01:08:06,040 --> 01:08:08,040
he's some horrible person?

818
01:08:14,080 --> 01:08:14,800
If you want to know

819
01:08:14,800 --> 01:08:15,880
what kind of person P'Jane really is,

820
01:08:15,880 --> 01:08:17,319
try calling this number.

821
01:08:19,359 --> 01:08:20,160
What number?

822
01:08:20,920 --> 01:08:22,439
If you want to ask P'Jane for something,

823
01:08:22,760 --> 01:08:24,040
this is the number you call.

824
01:08:24,040 --> 01:08:25,200
Then you'll finally find out

825
01:08:25,200 --> 01:08:26,840
all the trouble he caused.

826
01:09:10,120 --> 01:09:10,760
Well?

827
01:09:13,319 --> 01:09:14,439
What do you want to ask for?

828
01:09:15,840 --> 01:09:16,840
Just tell me.

829
01:09:26,960 --> 01:09:28,000
Please let me go. I'm begging you.

830
01:09:28,000 --> 01:09:28,760
Ow!

831
01:09:28,760 --> 01:09:29,479
I'm sorry.

832
01:09:29,479 --> 01:09:30,240
Please let me go.

833
01:09:30,319 --> 01:09:31,000
Hey!

834
01:09:31,359 --> 01:09:31,840
Stop!

835
01:09:32,680 --> 01:09:33,680
The reason I'm like this

836
01:09:34,319 --> 01:09:34,960
is because of P'Jane!!

837
01:09:35,240 --> 01:09:36,479
Do you know about Jui?

838
01:09:37,040 --> 01:09:38,279
Jui was abused by her ex-boyfriend.

839
01:09:39,560 --> 01:09:40,399
Serves her right.

840
01:09:46,120 --> 01:09:46,960
P'Jane!

841
01:09:48,359 --> 01:09:49,359
I'm not in the mood.

842
01:09:49,720 --> 01:09:51,160
I've already contacted someone

843
01:09:51,160 --> 01:09:52,880
who knows P'Jane's past for you.

844
01:09:53,399 --> 01:09:55,000
But he only wants to talk to you alone.

845
01:09:59,120 --> 01:10:00,200
Let's get straight to the point.

846
01:10:12,480 --> 01:10:16,880
You walk in with a warning sign

847
01:10:19,560 --> 01:10:24,440
Just one look and already falling for you

848
01:10:26,800 --> 01:10:31,640
My friends tell me not to cross that line

849
01:10:34,040 --> 01:10:38,840
But I’m already out of time

850
01:10:40,880 --> 01:10:42,880
I know the truth, I taste the sin

851
01:10:42,880 --> 01:10:44,560
It’s wrong but I don’t want it to be true

852
01:10:44,560 --> 01:10:47,240
I’m losing all my discipline

853
01:10:47,240 --> 01:10:51,160
You’re all I’m thinking of

854
01:10:51,160 --> 01:10:55,640
and I’m breaking all the rules just because…

855
01:10:55,640 --> 01:10:59,080
You’re a red flag but I’m colorblind

856
01:10:59,080 --> 01:11:02,320
I know you’re dangerous

857
01:11:02,880 --> 01:11:06,240
If it burns, let it burn me alive

858
01:11:06,240 --> 01:11:09,960
I can't hold myself back, I’d cross every line

859
01:11:09,960 --> 01:11:13,320
You’re a red flag but I’m colorblind

860
01:11:13,320 --> 01:11:16,800
I’d give up anything for you

861
01:11:17,120 --> 01:11:20,520
Even if it burns, I'm willing to melt away

862
01:11:20,520 --> 01:11:24,800
I can't hold myself back, I’d cross every line

863
01:11:32,040 --> 01:11:35,360
You can paint me with all your darkest sides

864
01:11:35,360 --> 01:11:38,920
And I’d still wear them like they’re paradise

865
01:11:38,920 --> 01:11:42,320
If this love is a perfect crime

866
01:11:42,320 --> 01:11:46,160
Then I’m guilty for life

867
01:11:46,160 --> 01:11:50,160
You tell me, don’t be too emotional that’s rule no. 1

868
01:11:50,560 --> 01:11:54,040
I’d give up everything to be your only one

869
01:11:54,280 --> 01:11:57,240
Ooh

870
01:11:57,320 --> 01:12:00,360
You’re the only one

